race.comment: LOOKING PRISTINE (8) settled back from out wide but wound up hard into the minor money, finishing 3 lengths from the winner (23.35) at Maitland in Grade 5. Sure to be about the mark. GRAND BLAZER (6) comes off an average effort last start when fifth at Richmond over 520m behind Tank Keeping (30.25) in a Grade 5. Has ability and can atone. PRIM AND PRETTY (2) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (26.81) in a Grade 5 at Bulli. Expected to give a good account. BOXCAR MOLLY (1) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.
